\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Cache extinction and federation composition.} (\textbf  {A})~Cache extinction: $TP^{-1}$ after caching on the linear $y$-axis versus uncached $TP^{-1}$ on the linear $x$-axis, $20$ trials. Navy circles are the cached evaluation, crimson dashed reference is the no-cache baseline. The structural drop --- mean speedup $1.16\times $, range $[1.07\times , 1.30\times ]$ --- corresponds to extinction of decision classes whose lookups become constant-time. This is the empirical content of Theorem~\ref {thm:cache-extinction}. (\textbf  {B})~Federation composition: composite $TP^{-1}_\mathrm  {fed}$ on the linear $y$-axis versus number of federated kernels $n \in \{1, \ldots  , 20\}$ on the linear $x$-axis, $40$ random federations. Navy circles are simulation; the curve saturates at $\Sigma $ from below. Maximum absolute residual against the closed-form $1 - TP^{-1}_\mathrm  {fed}/\Sigma = \DOTSB \prod@ \slimits@ _i (1 - TP^{-1}_i/\Sigma )$ is $0.0$. This is the empirical content of Theorem~\ref {thm:federation}. (\textbf  {C})~Diminishing returns: marginal $\Delta TP^{-1}$ from adding the $n$-th kernel on the linear $y$-axis versus $n \in \{1, \ldots  , 20\}$ on the linear $x$-axis, lightblue bars with navy edges. Bars decrease monotonically; final asymptote gap $\Sigma - TP^{-1}_\mathrm  {fed} = 7.98 \times 10^{-2}$ at $n=20$ confirms saturation. This is the empirical content of Corollary~\ref {cor:saturation}. (\textbf  {D})~Three-dimensional composition surface: $TP^{-1}_\mathrm  {fed}$ over $n \in \{1, \ldots  , 20\}$ and per-kernel $TP^{-1} \in [5, 95]$ at fixed $\Sigma = 100$, blues colourmap, viewing angle elevation $22^{\circ }$ azimuth $-58^{\circ }$. The upper plateau visualises the asymptotic ceiling that no finite federation can exceed.}}{15}{figure.caption.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:utl-panel-5}{{5}{15}{\textbf {Cache extinction and federation composition.} (\textbf {A})~Cache extinction: $TP^{-1}$ after caching on the linear $y$-axis versus uncached $TP^{-1}$ on the linear $x$-axis, $20$ trials. Navy circles are the cached evaluation, crimson dashed reference is the no-cache baseline. The structural drop --- mean speedup $1.16\times $, range $[1.07\times , 1.30\times ]$ --- corresponds to extinction of decision classes whose lookups become constant-time. This is the empirical content of Theorem~\ref {thm:cache-extinction}. (\textbf {B})~Federation composition: composite $TP^{-1}_\mathrm {fed}$ on the linear $y$-axis versus number of federated kernels $n \in \{1, \ldots , 20\}$ on the linear $x$-axis, $40$ random federations. Navy circles are simulation; the curve saturates at $\Sigma $ from below. Maximum absolute residual against the closed-form $1 - TP^{-1}_\mathrm {fed}/\Sigma = \prod _i (1 - TP^{-1}_i/\Sigma )$ is $0.0$. This is the empirical content of Theorem~\ref {thm:federation}. (\textbf {C})~Diminishing returns: marginal $\Delta TP^{-1}$ from adding the $n$-th kernel on the linear $y$-axis versus $n \in \{1, \ldots , 20\}$ on the linear $x$-axis, lightblue bars with navy edges. Bars decrease monotonically; final asymptote gap $\Sigma - TP^{-1}_\mathrm {fed} = 7.98 \times 10^{-2}$ at $n=20$ confirms saturation. This is the empirical content of Corollary~\ref {cor:saturation}. (\textbf {D})~Three-dimensional composition surface: $TP^{-1}_\mathrm {fed}$ over $n \in \{1, \ldots , 20\}$ and per-kernel $TP^{-1} \in [5, 95]$ at fixed $\Sigma = 100$, blues colourmap, viewing angle elevation $22^{\circ }$ azimuth $-58^{\circ }$. The upper plateau visualises the asymptotic ceiling that no finite federation can exceed}{figure.caption.7}{}}
